\(~\)

Introduction

\(~\)

As of 2021-10-19, the most recent number of daily tests reported was 1438 tests. There have now been 41220470 cumulative tests reported overall with a 7-day moving average of 50782 tests reported. The 7-day moving average for test positivity was 5 %.

The most recent number of reported cases was 1861 with a 7-day moving average of 2519. There have now been 3626142 reported for the State of Florida.

There are currently 2853 patients hospitalized in Florida with confirmed or suspected COVID-19. 2808 are adult patients and 45 are pediatric patients. There are currently 783 reported patients hospitalized in a staffed ICU bed with confirmed or suspected COVID-19.

68.2% of the population are now vaccinated with at least one dose. Of the age 12 and over population, 78.3% are now vaccinated with at least one dose. In addition, 97.7% of those 65 and older are now vaccinated with at least one dose.

The most recent number of deaths reported outside of the two-week delay was 68 and the 7-day moving average was 112.

Deaths per Day Graph

The following graph illustrates the case trajectory of COVID-19 in Florida.

Nota Bene: Information by date of death is the most timely and accurate presentation of mortality data. However, as a consequence of the reporting process, information over the past two - three weeks is highly provisional. For this reason, the most recent mortality information over the past two weeks is not included on the following graph and slope calculation. Information reported over the past two-weeks can be found in the above table for reference.

The most recent number of deaths reported outside of the two-week delay was 68 and the 7-day moving average was 112.

Over the past two weeks of complete data, the number of deaths reported has decreased by an an average of -10 fewer deaths reported each day

Data Sources

\(~\) Data sources are as follows:

  • COVID-19 Test Results: COVID-19 Diagnostic Laboratory Testing (PCR Testing) Time Seriers via U.S. Department of Health & Human Services. https://healthdata.gov/dataset/COVID-19-Diagnostic-Laboratory-Testing-PCR-Testing/j8mb-icvb

  • COVID-19 Hospital Census: COVID-19 Reported Patient Impact and Hospital Capacity by State via U.S. Department of Health & Human Services. https://healthdata.gov/dataset/COVID-19-Reported-Patient-Impact-and-Hospital-Capa/6xf2-c3ie

  • COVID-19 Vaccinations: COVID-19 Vaccinations in the United States, Jurisdiction via Center for Disease Control. https://data.cdc.gov/Vaccinations/COVID-19-Vaccinations-in-the-United-States-Jurisdi/unsk-b7fc

  • COVID-19 Cases and Deaths: United States COVID-19 Cases and Deaths by State over Time via Center for Disease Control Case Task Force. https://data.cdc.gov/Case-Surveillance/United-States-COVID-19-Cases-and-Deaths-by-State-o/9mfq-cb36
